  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective of the clinical trial is to evaluate the data of an app for smartphones
      (BiP-App) with regard to sleep, movement, mood and communication behavior.

      The data will be compared between two groups: people with a bipolar affective disorder and
      individuals without a psychiatric disorder.

      Secondary objective of the trial is to investigate if it is possible to detect early warning
      symptoms of depressive / (hypo) manic episodes via the measured behavior patterns.

      Furthermore it will be evaluated whether the BiP-app can find applicability in the examined
      patient group.

      Study design: Clinical evaluation of a medical device without CE mark; Parallel study design
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
